People check damaged buildings after the earthquakes in Malatya, Türkiye, on Feb. 6, 2023. At least 284 people were killed and 2,323 others injured after two strong earthquakes jolted Türkiye early Monday and damaged more than 1,700 buildings, Turkish Vice President Fuat Oktay said. (Photo by Mustafa Kaya/Xinhua) Xi sends condolences to Turkish, Syrian presidents over powerful earthquake in Turkey and Syria